					<h1>A Roadmap for New Physicians<br /><small>Avoiding Medicare and Medicaid Fraud and Abuse</small></h1>
				
					
				
<h2 class="line">Physician Education Training Materials</h2>


<p><img class="r" src="./images/phys_training_promo.png" alt="Booklet Cover" />The Office of Inspector General (OIG) for the U.S. Department of Health &amp; Human Services has created the educational materials listed below to assist in teaching physicians about the Federal
laws designed to protect the Medicare and Medicaid programs and program beneficiaries from fraud, waste, and abuse.</p>

<ul class="simplegray stay_blue">
<li><a target="_blank" href="/compliance/physician-education/roadmap_web_version.pdf"><em>A Roadmap for New Physicians: Avoiding Medicare and Medicaid Fraud and Abuse</em></a>&nbsp;<acronym title="Portable Document Format" class="file_type">(<a href="#pdf">PDF</a>)</acronym>,
which is a booklet for physicians' self-study.</li>
 
<li><a target="_blank" href="/compliance/physician-education/roadmap_powerpoint.ppt">A companion PowerPoint presentation</a>&nbsp;<acronym title="Microsoft PowerPoint" class="file_type">(PPT)</acronym> that we encourage you to use to teach the material contained in the Roadmap.</li>
 
