<p>These materials summarize the five main Federal fraud and abuse laws (the False Claims Act,
the Anti-Kickback Statute, the Stark Law, the Exclusion Statute, and the Civil Monetary
Penalties Law) and provides tips on how physicians should comply with these laws in their
relationships with payers (e.g., the Medicare and Medicaid programs), vendors (e.g., drug,
